      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FINAL PROMISE (9) broke in his first outing for the new yard two back but kept his manners in check at the latest appearance and showed what he is capable of, scoring by 3.5 metres at Newcastle. No favours expected from this draw but with even luck he could strike again. GENERAL LINCOLN (2) is a newcomer to the Josh Farrugia yard from Victoria. Didn't do a bad job when fourth at Melton last time out and draws well. LOUS PROMISE (10) has had three runs this prep without filling a placing but showed good improvement last time at Menangle, finishing less than 4 metres away. Draws out on the second line so may need luck but should be hitting peak fitness now. TOMMYS LUCK (7) draws for a trail and has claims off a brave second after racing wide at Menangle two starts ago.",
